{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-04019/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-04019"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:40:19"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["full shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, tracking"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman in a pink ballgown sits on a bench in an elegant room."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04019/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-04019","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04019/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-04019"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04019/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04019/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04019/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04019/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04019/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04019/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04019/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04019/canvas/1/ec922f3b-74e7-4e1f-9eca-95c4f94f39f1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T18:07:11.116Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Alma’s pose in this scene makes her resemble traditional painted portraiture, like those on the walls behind her. She is seated, with her hands clasped in her lap, with a neutral expression. This is a nod to Reynolds’s perception of his clothing as noble and grand. This is also a nod to Alma’s position as Reynolds’s muse, continuing the tradition of painters’ artistic muses, whose portraits they painted over and over.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04019/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:795.9084791386274,225.3835800807538,298.465679676985,608.5598923283983"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04019/canvas/1/1f98830c-42ab-4c2f-af72-c55ee120f2a7","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T18:07:26.688Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The figures in the paintings behind Alma face inward, as if looking at her. Alma is being photographed in this scene, with Reynolds and the photographer speaking to her as she sits. She is under the observation of everyone in the room, down to the paintings on the wall.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04019/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:1481.991924629879,50.95558546433384,328.18304172274566,317.8465679676985"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04019/canvas/1/790ceb62-f828-4ff8-873c-09ad2362251b","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T18:07:41.101Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Cornelius Johnson’s <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW223293641 BCX4\" href=\"https://www.npg.org.uk/collections/search/portrait/mw04599/Sir-Hugh-Myddelton-1st-Bt\"><u>1628 portrait of Welsh goldsmith, clothmaker, merchant, and Parliamentarian Sir Hugh Myddelton, 1st Baronet</u></a>, hangs above Alma on the left. Myddelton is perhaps best known for the 1609-1612 construction of the New River, an artificial waterway designed to bring clean water into London. Johnson, also known as Cornelis Janssens van Ceulen, was born to Dutch parents in London in 1593 and trained in the Netherlands before returning to the city of his birth. Primarily associated with images of the gentry class, Johnson was one of the most prominent painters of portraits in England before the arrival of Anthony Van Dyck in 1632.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04019/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:177.0121130551817,32.866756393001424,257.1197846567968,293.29744279946163"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04019/canvas/1/28b49a0b-05ee-4a05-aa12-2c85651cfeca","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T18:07:54.833Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The camera once again pulls in toward Alma, both from the front and the back, mirroring Reynolds’s fierce gaze from the doorway. He takes her in just as viewers do, too.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04019/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:162.79946164199177,419.19246298788704,366.94481830417226,240.3230148048453"}}}]}]}]}